News.Title: Euro India Fresh Foods Reports 87% Drop in Q1 Net Profit
News.Summary: Euro India Fresh Foods reported Q1 net profit of 3.3 million rupees, down from 25.8 million rupees in the same period last year. Revenue declined to 311.7 million rupees from 349.8 million rupees year-over-year. EBITDA fell to 22.2 million rupees compared to 49.5 million rupees previously, with EBITDA margin contracting to 7.12% from 14.15% in the prior year period.

News.Title: Euro India Fresh Foods Reports Q3 Financial Results
News.Summary: Euro India Fresh Foods has announced its financial results for the third quarter. The company reported a net profit of 18 million rupees, up from 11 million rupees in the same period last year. Revenue for Q3 increased to 478 million rupees, compared to 301 million rupees in the previous year's corresponding quarter.
